idlc-go is a clean-room reimplementation of `idlc.jar`, the IDL compiler
distributed with SWGEmu's `engine3` framework
(https://github.com/swgemu/MMOEngine). idlc-go was written from scratch by
inspecting the JAR's textual output and the `.idl` corpus inside SWGEmu's
Core3 server (https://github.com/swgemu/Core3); no decompiled or
reverse-engineered source code from the JAR was incorporated.

The reference `idlc.jar` is not redistributed with this project. It is
referenced from a Core3 / engine3 checkout at runtime for oracle-based
testing only.

The C++ output produced by idlc-go is governed by the licenses of the
`.idl` source files supplied as input. When idlc-go is used to compile
SWGEmu Core3 / engine3 IDLs, that output inherits those projects'
AGPL-3.0 license.
